race.comment: Looks an ideal assignment for AVENUES (1). Fitter for two runs back and will find this much easier than last time at Cranbourne. Goes very well third-up and the extra ground a plus. Gets chance. DISCOBAY (9) came off a poor run two back with a solid fourth last time. Has early speed and a low draw and will be in this for a long way. FIRST THOUGHT (3) is a lightly raced type who relished the extra ground last time when heavily bet and scored maiden win. Fitter again and has upside. Worth following up. DA DEPUTY (8) was outclassed over 3000m in much tougher grade last time but the start prior an effortless picnic winner. Has the ability and can bounce back this easier grade. MASTER POLANSKI (11) is coming off a picnic win but prior to that was racing in similar grade to this and knocking on the door. Confidence back and drops 10kg on the win.
